Here, sir. Use mine.

734
01:02:59,757 --> 01:03:03,719
Senator Martin, Dr. Hannibal Lecter.

735
01:03:08,974 --> 01:03:10,184
Dr. Lecter.

736
01:03:10,976 --> 01:03:13,979
I brought an affidavit
guaranteeing your new rights.

737
01:03:14,605 --> 01:03:16,732
You'll want to read it before I sign.

738
01:03:20,903 --> 01:03:24,740
I won't waste your time or Catherine's time
bargaining for petty privileges.

739
01:03:25,324 --> 01:03:27,386
Clarice Starling
and that awful Jack Crawford

740
01:03:27,410 --> 01:03:29,203
have wasted far too much time already.

741
01:03:29,870 --> 01:03:32,248
I only pray
they haven't doomed the poor girl.

742
01:03:33,833 --> 01:03:37,145
Let me help you now,
and I will trust you when it is all over.

743
01:03:37,169 --> 01:03:39,004
You have my word. Paul?

744
01:03:42,258 --> 01:03:44,802
Buffalo Bill's real name is Louis Friend.

745
01:03:45,845 --> 01:03:47,239
I met him just once.

746
01:03:47,263 --> 01:03:52,393
He was referred to me in April or May 1980
by my patient Benjamin Raspail.

747
01:03:53,185 --> 01:03:54,687
They were lovers, you see.

748
01:03:55,479 --> 01:03:59,066
But Raspail had become very frightened.

749
01:03:59,608 --> 01:04:02,820
Apparently, Louis had murdered a transient

750
01:04:03,404 --> 01:04:06,449
and done things with the skin.

751
01:04:07,658 --> 01:04:10,244
We need his address
and a physical description.

752
01:04:11,579 --> 01:04:12,997
Tell me, Senator,

753
01:04:13,873 --> 01:04:16,351
did you nurse Catherine yourself?

754
01:04:16,375 --> 01:04:18,961
- What?
- Did you breast-feed her?

755
01:04:19,462 --> 01:04:21,982
- Wait a minute.
- Yes, I did.

756
01:04:22,006 --> 01:04:25,509
- Toughened your nipples, didn't it?
- You son of a bitch!

757
01:04:26,093 --> 01:04:29,906
Amputate a man's leg,
and he can still feel it tickling.

758
01:04:29,930 --> 01:04:35,060
Tell me, Mom, when your little girl
is on the slab, where will it tickle you?

759
01:04:35,769 --> 01:04:38,856
Take this thing back to Baltimore.

760
01:04:40,232 --> 01:04:43,378
Five-foot-ten, strongly built,
about 180 pounds.

761
01:04:43,402 --> 01:04:47,591
Hair blond, eyes pale blue.
He'd be about 35 now.

762
01:04:47,615 --> 01:04:50,075
He said he lived in Philadelphia
but may have lied.

763
01:04:50,659 --> 01:04:52,679
That's all I can remember, Mom.

764
01:04:52,703 --> 01:04:55,414
But if I think of any more,
I will let you know.

765
01:04:57,917 --> 01:05:00,294
Oh, and, Senator, just one more thing.

766
01:05:02,713 --> 01:05:04,215
Love your suit.

767
01:05:06,425 --> 01:05:08,695
I can tell you now
that in a meeting earlier this evening

768
01:05:08,719 --> 01:05:13,158
with Senator Ruth Martin, Dr. Lecter
agreed to assist in the investigation

769
01:05:13,182 --> 01:05:16,328
of trying to find the abductor
of Catherine Martin, Buffalo Bill.

770
01:05:16,352 --> 01:05:18,580
- How do you fit in, sir?
- It's through my unique insight

771
01:05:18,604 --> 01:05:20,707
into Lecter's mind
that this breakthrough was possible.

772
01:05:20,731 --> 01:05:22,000
And Buffalo Bill's real name?

773
01:05:22,024 --> 01:05:25,962
Buffalo Bill's real name is now a matter
of record with the proper authorities.

774
01:05:25,986 --> 01:05:28,632
- Can you give us more information?
- My name is Dr. Frederick Chilton.

775
01:05:28,656 --> 01:05:30,199
- How do you spell that?
- That's C-H -

776
01:05:31,784 --> 01:05:33,285
Are you with Dr. Chilton's group?

777
01:05:34,036 --> 01:05:36,038
Uh, well, I just saw him outside, sir.

778
01:05:36,705 --> 01:05:40,268
Access to Lecter is strictly limited.
We've been getting death threats.

779
01:05:40,292 --> 01:05:41,835
I understand, sir.

780
01:05:47,967 --> 01:05:49,593
Log in and check your weapon.

781
01:05:51,011 --> 01:05:53,406
I can't take all the credit for myself.

782
01:05:53,430 --> 01:05:55,200
Senator Martin, the Justice Department,

783
01:05:55,224 --> 01:05:58,245
people at the FBI,
the folks at the Baltimore State Hospital.

784
01:05:58,269 --> 01:06:00,813
And now for the hard part,
apprehending the suspect.

785
01:06:01,814 --> 01:06:04,275
Excuse me, folks. I have to catch a flight.

786
01:06:08,279 --> 01:06:09,905
Command desk. Officer Jacobs.

787
01:06:19,206 --> 01:06:21,917
- Is it true what they're saying?
- Huh?

788
01:06:23,294 --> 01:06:25,462
He's some kind of vampire.

789
01:06:27,715 --> 01:06:30,860
They don't have a name for what he is.

790
01:06:30,884 --> 01:06:32,720
You do know the rules, ma'am?

791
01:06:33,387 --> 01:06:35,764
Yes, Lieutenant Boyle.
I've questioned him before.

792
01:06:39,184 --> 01:06:40,269
Go ahead.

793
01:07:17,514 --> 01:07:19,183
Good evening, Clarice.

794
01:07:21,143 --> 01:07:23,354
I thought you might like
your drawings back, Doctor.

795
01:07:26,565 --> 01:07:28,359
Just until you get your view.

796
01:07:29,360 --> 01:07:31,195
How very thoughtful.

797
01:07:32,696 --> 01:07:35,634
Or did Jack Crawford
send you for one last wheedle

798
01:07:35,658 --> 01:07:37,826
before you're both booted off the case?

799
01:07:38,410 --> 01:07:40,245
No, I came because I wanted to.

800
01:07:45,209 --> 01:07:47,628
People will say we're in love.

801
01:07:48,629 --> 01:07:51,256
Tsk, tsk, tsk, tsk, tsk,
tsk, tsk, tsk, tsk, tsk.

802
01:07:51,757 --> 01:07:53,884
Anthrax Island.

803
01:07:54,551 --> 01:07:57,054
That was an especially nice touch,
Clarice.

804
01:07:57,638 --> 01:07:58,639
Yours?

805
01:07:59,390 --> 01:08:00,492
Yes.

806
01:08:00,516 --> 01:08:02,017
Yeah.

807
01:08:02,685 --> 01:08:04,186
That was good.

808
01:08:04,895 --> 01:08:09,042
Pity about poor Catherine though.
Ticktock, ticktock, ticktock, ticktock.

809
01:08:09,066 --> 01:08:11,443
Your anagrams are showing, Doctor.

810
01:08:12,861 --> 01:08:15,048
Louis Friend?

811
01:08:15,072 --> 01:08:18,301
Iron sulfide, also known as fool's gold.

812
01:08:18,325 --> 01:08:22,579
Oh, Clarice, your problem is
you need to get more fun out of life.

813
01:08:23,163 --> 01:08:25,416
You were telling me the truth
back in Baltimore, sir.

814
01:08:26,166 --> 01:08:27,418
Please continue now.

815
01:08:28,210 --> 01:08:30,295
I've read the case files. Have you?

816
01:08:31,213 --> 01:08:34,275
Everything you need to find him
is right there in those pages.

817
01:08:34,299 --> 01:08:37,404
- Then tell me how.
- First principles, Clarice.

818
01:08:37,428 --> 01:08:39,239
Simplicity.

819
01:08:39,263 --> 01:08:40,782
Read Marcus Aurelius.

820
01:08:40,806 --> 01:08:43,976
Of each particular thing, ask,
what is it in itself?

821
01:08:44,518 --> 01:08:45,811
What is its nature?

822
01:08:46,603 --> 01:08:50,649
What does he do, this man you seek?

823
01:08:52,067 --> 01:08:53,461
He kills women.

824
01:08:53,485 --> 01:08:56,530
No. That is incidental.

825
01:08:57,614 --> 01:08:59,426
What is the first
and principal thing he does?

826
01:08:59,450 --> 01:09:02,721
What needs does he serve by killing?

827
01:09:02,745 --> 01:09:04,222
Anger.

828
01:09:04,246 --> 01:09:10,645
Um... social acceptance
and, um, sexual frustration, sir.

829
01:09:10,669 --> 01:09:13,338
No. He covets.

830
01:09:14,757 --> 01:09:16,341
That is his nature.

831
01:09:16,925 --> 01:09:19,178
And how do we begin to covet, Clarice?

832
01:09:19,887 --> 01:09:21,972
Do we seek out things to covet?

833
01:09:23,140 --> 01:09:25,243
Make an effort to answer now.

834
01:09:25,267 --> 01:09:28,079
No. We just -

835
01:09:28,103 --> 01:09:31,416
No. We begin by coveting
what we see every day.

836
01:09:31,440 --> 01:09:34,777
Don't you feel eyes
moving over your body, Clarice?

837
01:09:35,527 --> 01:09:38,906
And don't your eyes
seek out the things you want?

838
01:09:39,615 --> 01:09:42,010
All right, yes. Now please tell me how.

839
01:09:42,034 --> 01:09:43,327
No.

840
01:09:44,244 --> 01:09:48,999
It is your turn to tell me, Clarice.
You don't have any more vacations to sell.

841
01:09:49,666 --> 01:09:51,752
Why did you leave that ranch?

842
01:09:52,461 --> 01:09:56,006
Doctor, we don't have any more time
for any of this now.

843
01:09:56,673 --> 01:09:59,402
But we don't reckon time
the same way, do we, Clarice?

844
01:09:59,426 --> 01:10:01,404
This is all the time you'll ever have.

845
01:10:01,428 --> 01:10:03,865
Later. Now, please, listen to me.
We've only got five -

846
01:10:03,889 --> 01:10:07,267
No! I will listen now.

847
01:10:09,478 --> 01:10:12,707
After your father's murder, you were
orphaned. You were 10 years old.

848
01:10:12,731 --> 01:10:15,818
You went to live with cousins
on a sheep and horse ranch in Montana.

849
01:10:16,485 --> 01:10:17,486
And?

850
01:10:19,696 --> 01:10:21,949
And one morning, I just ran away.

851
01:10:22,741 --> 01:10:26,179
Not “just,” Clarice. What set you off?

852
01:10:26,203 --> 01:10:28,038
You started at what time?

853
01:10:28,705 --> 01:10:30,141
Early. Still dark.

854
01:10:30,165 --> 01:10:33,061
Then something woke you, didn't it?
Was it a dream?

855
01:10:33,085 --> 01:10:34,169
What was it?

856
01:10:35,712 --> 01:10:37,464
I heard a strange noise.

857
01:10:38,715 --> 01:10:40,092
What was it?

858
01:10:40,676 --> 01:10:41,760
It was...

859
01:10:43,095 --> 01:10:44,429
screaming.

860
01:10:46,181 --> 01:10:48,892
Some kind of screaming,
like a child's voice.

861
01:10:49,476 --> 01:10:50,936
What did you do?

862
01:10:51,520 --> 01:10:55,190
I went downstairs, outside.

863
01:10:57,818 --> 01:10:59,653
I crept up into the barn house.

864
01:11:00,654 --> 01:11:03,448
I was so scared to look inside,
but I had to.

865
01:11:04,616 --> 01:11:06,719
What did you see, Clarice?

866
01:11:06,743 --> 01:11:08,287
What did you see?

867
01:11:09,746 --> 01:11:10,956
Lambs.

868
01:11:12,207 --> 01:11:13,876
They were screaming.

869
01:11:14,459 --> 01:11:17,272
They were slaughtering the spring lambs?

870
01:11:17,296 --> 01:11:19,047
And they were screaming.

871
01:11:20,799 --> 01:11:22,735
And you ran away?

872
01:11:22,759 --> 01:11:23,760
No.

873
01:11:24,511 --> 01:11:26,513
First I tried to free them. I -

874
01:11:27,222 --> 01:11:29,784
I opened the gate to their pen,
but they wouldn't run.

875
01:11:29,808 --> 01:11:32,978
They just stood there, confused.
They wouldn't run.

876
01:11:33,562 --> 01:11:35,647
But you could, and you did, didn't you?

877
01:11:36,773 --> 01:11:38,084
Yes.

878
01:11:38,108 --> 01:11:40,461
I took one lamb
and I ran away as fast as I could.

879
01:11:40,485 --> 01:11:42,380
Where were you going, Clarice?

880
01:11:42,404 --> 01:11:46,843
I don't know. I didn't have any food,
any water, and it was very cold.

881
01:11:46,867 --> 01:11:48,076
It was very cold.

882
01:11:50,412 --> 01:11:51,413
I thought -

883
01:11:52,456 --> 01:11:54,666
I thought if I could save just one, but...

884
01:11:57,044 --> 01:11:58,420
he was so heavy.

885
01:11:59,630 --> 01:12:01,131
He was so heavy.

886
01:12:06,553 --> 01:12:10,265
I didn't get more than a few miles
when the sheriffs car picked me up.

887
01:12:13,727 --> 01:12:17,481
Rancher was so angry, he sent me to live
at the Lutheran orphanage in Bozeman.

888
01:12:18,690 --> 01:12:20,359
I never saw the ranch again.

889
01:12:21,068 --> 01:12:24,154
What became of your lamb, Clarice?

890
01:12:26,114 --> 01:12:27,717
They killed him.

891
01:12:27,741 --> 01:12:30,011
You still wake up sometimes, don't you?

892
01:12:30,035 --> 01:12:31,828
Wake up in the dark

893
01:12:32,663 --> 01:12:35,457
and hear the screaming of the lambs.

894
01:12:36,041 --> 01:12:37,042
Yes.

895
01:12:38,752 --> 01:12:43,066
And you think if you saved poor Catherine,
you could make them stop, don't you?

896
01:12:43,090 --> 01:12:45,443
You think, if Catherine lives,

897
01:12:45,467 --> 01:12:47,803
you won't wake up in the dark ever again...

898
01:12:48,804 --> 01:12:51,723
to that awful screaming of the lambs.

899
01:12:52,891 --> 01:12:55,852
I don't know. I don't know.

900
01:12:57,938 --> 01:13:00,107
Thank you, Clarice.

901
01:13:00,774 --> 01:13:02,251
Thank you.

902
01:13:02,275 --> 01:13:03,944
Tell me his name, Doctor.

903
01:13:11,201 --> 01:13:13,286
Dr. Chilton, I presume?

904
01:13:14,287 --> 01:13:15,872
I think you know each other.

905
01:13:18,083 --> 01:13:19,334
Okay.

906
01:13:20,252 --> 01:13:22,004
- We found her.
- Let's go.

907
01:13:22,504 --> 01:13:24,006
It's your turn, Doctor.

908
01:13:24,756 --> 01:13:26,734
- Out.
- Tell me his name.

909
01:13:26,758 --> 01:13:29,529
Sorry, ma'am, I've got orders.
Have to put you on a plane.

910
01:13:29,553 --> 01:13:31,114
Come on now.

911
01:13:31,138 --> 01:13:32,723
Brave Clarice.

912
01:13:33,432 --> 01:13:37,078
You will let me know when those lambs
stop screaming, won't you?

913
01:13:37,102 --> 01:13:39,163
Tell me his name, Doctor.

914
01:13:39,187 --> 01:13:40,522
Clarice!

915
01:13:41,815 --> 01:13:43,316
Your case file.

916
01:13:45,402 --> 01:13:46,403
Hey.

917
01:13:48,447 --> 01:13:50,115
Good-bye, Clarice.

918
01:14:56,223 --> 01:14:58,076
Ready when you are, Doc.

919
01:14:58,100 --> 01:15:00,185
Just another minute, please.

920
01:15:09,361 --> 01:15:12,048
Son of a bitch demanded a second dinner.

921
01:15:12,072 --> 01:15:13,925
Lamb chops. Extra rare.

922
01:15:13,949 --> 01:15:18,453
Wonder what he wants for breakfast.
Some damn thing from the zoo?

923
01:15:40,100 --> 01:15:41,702
Good evening, gentlemen.

924
01:15:41,726 --> 01:15:43,996
Okay, Doc. Grab some floor.

925
01:15:44,020 --> 01:15:46,106
- Same drill as before, please.
- Mm-hmm.

926
01:15:52,988 --> 01:15:54,990
Ready when you are, Sergeant Pembry.

927
01:16:11,840 --> 01:16:13,049
Okay.

928
01:16:19,806 --> 01:16:21,808
- Hand me that, would you?
- Uh-huh.

929
01:16:26,980 --> 01:16:28,190
Thanks.

930
01:16:32,110 --> 01:16:33,695
Mind the drawings, please.

931
01:16:37,115 --> 01:16:38,325
Thank you.

932
01:17:02,807 --> 01:17:04,517
Jimmy, watch it! He's got me!

933
01:17:11,900 --> 01:17:13,568
Jesus Christ!

934
01:17:24,496 --> 01:17:26,122
I need help.

935
01:18:32,314 --> 01:18:34,482
Ready when you are, Sergeant Pembry.

936
01:18:44,200 --> 01:18:46,369
What is this shit?

937
01:18:48,580 --> 01:18:50,433
Did somebody go up on five?

938
01:18:50,457 --> 01:18:52,893
No. Nobody went up.

939
01:18:52,917 --> 01:18:55,754
Call Pembry. Ask him to tell -

940
01:18:56,880 --> 01:18:59,358
<i>GP. Shots fired on five.</i>

941
01:18:59,382 --> 01:19:01,485
Repeat, shots fired on five.

942
01:19:01,509 --> 01:19:02,844
Sergeant Tate!

943
01:19:03,428 --> 01:19:05,698
<i>Shots fired on five.</i>

944
01:19:05,722 --> 01:19:08,367
- Holy shit!
- What the hell?

945
01:19:08,391 --> 01:19:10,745
- Shut up!

946
01:19:10,769 --> 01:19:12,204
Bobby, get the vest.

947
01:19:12,228 --> 01:19:13,438
Right, Sarge.

948
01:19:14,147 --> 01:19:16,483
- Brady, Howard, cover the -
- Look!

949
01:19:17,609 --> 01:19:20,653
It stopped.

950
01:19:21,988 --> 01:19:23,758
Seal off a 10-block radius.

951
01:19:23,782 --> 01:19:26,594
Get me the SWAT team
and an ambulance, double quick.

952
01:19:26,618 --> 01:19:27,911
We're goin' up.

953
01:19:57,190 --> 01:19:59,192
Pembry!

954
01:20:00,193 --> 01:20:02,195
Boyle!

955
01:20:14,707 --> 01:20:15,959
Oh, God!

956
01:20:23,049 --> 01:20:24,467
Go.

957
01:20:31,933 --> 01:20:33,452
- Clear.
- Clear.

958
01:20:33,476 --> 01:20:36,479
Command post, two officers down.

959
01:20:37,063 --> 01:20:38,707
- Clear.
- Clear!

960
01:20:38,731 --> 01:20:40,376
Lecter's gone, Sarge.

961
01:20:40,400 --> 01:20:42,378
Prisoner is missing.

962
01:20:42,402 --> 01:20:46,799
- Boyle's gun is gone, Sergeant.
- Repeat, Lecter's missing and armed.

963
01:20:46,823 --> 01:20:49,051
He's stripped the bed.

964
01:20:49,075 --> 01:20:51,411
Might be making a rope. Check all windows.

965
01:20:51,995 --> 01:20:54,515
Where the fuck is my ambulance?

966
01:20:54,539 --> 01:20:56,124
He's alive.

967
01:20:57,041 --> 01:20:59,353
Sergeant Tate, he's alive!

968
01:20:59,377 --> 01:21:02,297
Get a hold of him where
you can feel his hands, son. Talk to him.

969
01:21:03,423 --> 01:21:04,483
What do I say?

970
01:21:04,507 --> 01:21:07,010
It's Jim Pembry! Now talk to him, damn it!

971
01:21:08,219 --> 01:21:10,739
Lecter's missing and armed.

972
01:21:10,763 --> 01:21:13,284
Pembry. Pembry, can you hear me?

973
01:21:13,308 --> 01:21:18,038
He took Boyle's gun. Pembry got off one
round. There's a chance Lecter was hit.

974
01:21:18,062 --> 01:21:20,416
Keep breathing in and out. That's it.

975
01:21:20,440 --> 01:21:23,443
You're doing a good job.
Oh, you look real good there.

976
01:21:24,527 --> 01:21:27,489
Yeah, you look... real good.

977
01:21:44,422 --> 01:21:45,691
- You ready?
- Let's go.

978
01:21:45,715 --> 01:21:47,300
- Let's do it.
- Okay? Let's go.

979
01:21:52,931 --> 01:21:54,349
- Got it?
- Yeah.

980
01:21:58,686 --> 01:22:00,748
Lookin' good, Pembry.
You're gonna make it.

981
01:22:00,772 --> 01:22:03,250
You're doin' just fine.
You're doin' all right. That's right.

982
01:22:03,274 --> 01:22:05,586
- Okay, I need that IV now!
- Lactated Ringer's.

983
01:22:05,610 --> 01:22:08,172
Can we get the strap?
